timeline.bodyText:
This seems brittle. If we are want to ensure the service has started before running the test,
Could you do something like:
boolean started = false;
Object waiter = new Object();
Thread t = new Thread(() -> {
  deploymentService.startup();
  synchronized (waiter) {
    started = true;
    waiter.notify();
  }
);
t.start();

synchronized (waiter) {
  while (!started) {
    waiter.wait();
  }
}
// deploymentService has started now

